This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image captioning and visual attention. It also involves Natural Language Processing (NLP) as it uses associated captions to guide attention, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The paper proposes an exemplar-based learning approach, which involves machine learning techniques, indicating that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of attention mechanisms, which is a popular technique in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) research. Finally, the paper evaluates its model's performance using standard metrics, which suggests that it could also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
